    <settingList>
        <setting>
            <title>Trigon's World</title>
            <p>They walk the streets of Trigon's World where everyone lives in fear. A little girl calls Trigon a monster and he makes her an example by killing her in front of everyone.</p>
            <charsPresent>
                <char ref="#raven">Raven</char>
                <char ref="#trigon">Trigon</char>
                <char ref="#ruda">Ruda</char>
            </charsPresent>
        </setting>
        <setting>
            <title>Trigon's Castle</title>
            <p>Grool has a status report for Trigon; Xynthia is fighting against his forces and refuse to pay him any longer. To teach another lesson to his subjects, Trigon destroys Xynthia. His next move is to destroy Earth.</p>
            <charsPresent>
                <char ref="#raven">Raven</char>
                <char ref="#trigon">Trigon</char>
                <char ref="#queenxyn">Queen of Xynthia</char>
                <char ref="#darkhorde">Dark Horde(s)</char>
                <char ref="#grool">Grool</char>
            </charsPresent>
        </setting>
        <setting>
            <title>Temple Azarath</title>
            <p>Trigon has destroyed Azarath and the Titans are reflecting on the battle that they lost. Determined to save Raven, they seek for help, but Arella and Azarath refused to provide it. The Titans persist and Arella provides a look into her past of Trigon and Azarath through flashback. Afterwards Arella decides to help the Titans save Raven, giving up her home in the process.</p>
            <charsPresent>
                <char ref="#robin">Robin</char>
                <char ref="#cyborg">Victor Stone</char>
                <char ref="#wgirl">Wonder Girl</char>
                <char ref="#kflash">Kid Flash</char>
                <char ref="#bboy">Beast Boy</char>
                <char ref="#starfire">Koriand'r</char>
                <char ref="#arella">Arella</char>
                <char ref="#priestAza">Priests of Azarath</char>
                <char ref="#priestSat">Priests of Satan</char>
                <char ref="#coman">Coman</char>
            </charsPresent>
        </setting>
        <setting>
            <title>Cosmic Stairway</title>
            <p>The Titans and Arella use the Great Door for dimensional travel to go to the new world that Raven resides.</p>
            <charsPresent>
                <char ref="#arella">Arella</char>
                <char ref="#robin">Robin</char>
                <char ref="#cyborg">Victor Stone</char>
                <char ref="#wgirl">Wonder Girl</char>
                <char ref="#kflash">Kid Flash</char>
                <char ref="#bboy">Beast Boy</char>
                <char ref="#starfire">Koriand'r</char>
            </charsPresent>
        </setting>
        <setting>
            <title>Trigon's Planet</title>
            <p>They arrive and Arella senses Raven. Kid Flash decides to use his speed to get there quicker, but they run into Trigon and his dog Fang. They go to battle him, but fall unconsicous due to Fang's bark. A Guard reveals that Raven is missing.</p>
            <charsPresent>
                <char ref="#arella">Arella</char>
                <char ref="#robin">Robin</char>
                <char ref="#cyborg">Victor Stone</char>
                <char ref="#wgirl">Wonder Girl</char>
                <char ref="#kflash">Kid Flash</char>
                <char ref="#bboy">Beast Boy</char>
                <char ref="#starfire">Koriand'r</char>
                <char ref="#fang">Fang</char>
                <char ref="#darkhorde">Dark Horde(s)</char>
            </charsPresent>
        </setting>
        <setting>
            <title>Dark Alleyway</title>
            <p>Arella is the one who helped Raven escape. Trigon sends demons to find her, destroying anything and anyone who stands in the way. Raven, who can't take the suffering, surrenders to Trigon. Arella strikes Trigon in an attempt to let Raven get away, but Trigon stops Raven. Arella supresses Trigon long enough for Raven to get away.</p>
            <charsPresent>
                <char ref="#arella">Arella</char>
                <char ref="#raven">Raven</char>
                <char ref="#trigon">Trigon</char>
            </charsPresent>
        </setting>
        <setting>
            <title>Dungeon</title>
            <p>Raven rescues the Titans from Trigon's Dungeon. It's time to return to Earth.</p>
            <charsPresent>
                <char ref="#raven">Raven</char>
                <char ref="#robin">Robin</char>
                <char ref="#kflash">Kid Flash</char>
                <char ref="#starfire">Koriand'r</char>
                <char ref="#wgirl">Wonder Girl</char>
                <char ref="#bboy">Beast Boy</char>
                <char ref="#cyborg">Victor Stone</char>
            </charsPresent>
        </setting>
        <setting>
            <title>Elsewhere</title>
            <p>Trigon is ready to attack Planet Earth for his plan of conquering a new dimension.</p>
            <charsPresent>
                <char ref="#trigon">Trigon</char>
            </charsPresent>
        </setting>
        <setting>
            <title>The Streets of Trigon's Planet</title>
            <p>The Titans are urgently trying to escape when they run into his dog, Fang; they leave Beast Boy to deal with him. Their plan is to combine their powers in order to send Trigon to the Netherverse. It works, but at the last minute, Arella jumps in after Trigon before the portal explodes. Raven reveals that in order to keep Trigon from escaping, someone had to block his path and that person was Arella.</p>
            <charsPresent>
                <char ref="#raven">Raven</char>
                <char ref="#kflash">Kid Flash</char>
                <char ref="#robin">Robin</char>
                <char ref="#bboy">Beast Boy</char>
                <char ref="#cyborg">Victor Stone</char>
                <char ref="#wgirl">Wonder Girl</char>
                <char ref="#starfire">Koriand'r</char>
                <char ref="#fang">Fang</char>
                <char ref="#trigon">Trigon</char>
                <char ref="#arella">Arella</char>
            </charsPresent>
        </setting>
